(406, 1, '2019-02-06 15:25:18', '2019-02-06 15:25:18', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mama, Wife, Marriage and Family Therapist, Network Marketer, App Developer, Entrepreneur, Coach..key words that describe who I am and what I do. Yet kinda a dime a dozen, right? There are plenty of women out there who carry the same titles and do similar things. However, what distinguishes me from them?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s personal branding.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And believe it or not, personal branding is very important to my success. Because without it, I am buried beneath all the other on line entrepreneurs. Personal branding lets me establish a reputation and voice while (hopefully!) attaining trust and allowing interaction between me and my market or target audience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When people deem you likeable, friendly, helpful, genuine, and sincere, they may do business with you. They may become a customer. They may become a business partner. And if you\'re in the on line business space (and I believe this also applies to brick and mortar businesses!), chances are you\'re more than likely looking for customers and/or business partners.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s face it. Our modern society questions the motives of businesses and corporations. We see them as wanting to make a sale, increase profits, etc. and taking the actions necessary to reach their goals (advertising, commercials, email marketing, etc.) Sometimes it can get overwhelming and we tune their efforts out. Nowadays there are more options for learning about companies, products and services by way of social media platforms and we often choose this route because it\'s at our fingertips.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The truth is, we the consumers, are more likely to trust people instead of corporations these days. We look for recommendations from friends, influencers, and celebrities, but not just anyone. We look to those we know, like and trust.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How do you become someone that others go to for suggestions, advice or recommendations? How do you grow your influence factor?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You build your personal brand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, it doesn\'t happen overnight and to be honest, there is strategy involved. Yet, it\'s not rocket science.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s get you started in building your personal brand!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1. Identify Your Target Audience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I highly recommend you get very specific on your target audience. Who do you want to attract to you? What value do you have to offer them? What content would you like to share?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a partner&nbsp;with a health and wellness company, the products I share can help anyone. Yet, when I marketed to everyone, I got nowhere fast. I had to get very specific on my niche. I had to hang out in networks or groups where my target audience was spending time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And I also had to get into their heads and think like them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What are their pain points?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What are their struggles, challenges and obstacles?<br>What do they desire?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What have they already tried?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once I was able to answer these questions, I moved on to the next step.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. Create valuable content specifically for your target audience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that I knew WHO I was targeting and what their needs were, I could come up with endless content!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s take the example of hair care products and you\'ve decided to focus on women, 30+, possibly moms, working outside of the home, active, social and love to have fun. (Here\'s a hint. Look in the mirror, a lot of the time, we are our own target audience! We know this niche really well, right? Maybe your products have solved similar problems for you?)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Based on this population, your ideas for valuable content are infinite!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Easy and quick hair styles for on the go lifestyles</li><li>Benefits of all natural hair care</li><li>How to look your best in under 30 minutes</li><li>Fashion trends for moms</li><li>20 minutes to get ready for work? No problem!</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These are all just off the top of my head. Imagine what you could come up with if you gave yourself 30-40 minutes of brainstorming? I want to encourage you to also share content outside of your products, services and business. Sprinkle in other topics you love.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Get consistent on posting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If there\'s one thing I preach to the team, it\'s this – “Consistency is queen and content is king!”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I am at the Publix (which is probably 3 days a week!), it never fails that I run into someone who says, “I saw your post the other day on...”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I also often hear, “Lisa, every time I get on Facebook, your posts are at the top of my feed.” Get consistent on sharing valuable content because people are logging on and off Facebook all day long! You want to be at the top of their feeds. And just because they aren\'t clicking like or leaving a comment – that doesn\'t mean they aren\'t seeing your posts. A lot of people prefer to \'stalk\' and be invisible on social media.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I recommend posting on Facebook 3-5 times a day. I suggest sharing a variety of topics that pertain to your brand. Lifestyle, career, family, hobbies, pets, etc. Limit your business and product posts to 3-5 times a week. (Remember, when sharing your business and product posts, you want to share the BENEFITS of your services and products.)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can create your personal brand. It will take time yet it\'s so worth it. Remember NOTHING happens overnight. For us to be better at anything, we have to consistently work on it. Relationships, parenting, hobbies, health and wellness, etc...they all take time and plenty of energy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Receive my free gift - 8 Must Knows for Personal Branding&nbsp;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/7secretssocialmediamakeover\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">HERE</a>!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Struggling to determine your personal brand? I know the feeling! After almost 2 years of studying and building my own brand, I offer one on one coaching. See if we\'re a good fit by filling out this&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/H8MK97J\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">form&nbsp;</a>and I\'ll be in touch with you soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":403,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://handspeak.web-art.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/post1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-403\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode /-->', 'Why A Personal Brand Is Important', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '402-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-02-06 15:25:18', '2019-02-06 15:25:18', '', 402, 'http://handspeak.web-art.net/402-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(411, 1, '2019-02-06 15:29:04', '2019-02-06 15:29:04', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Content is key to building your personal brand. Yet, so many people tell me they struggle with creating it! I truly understand&nbsp;though because a few years ago I would sit for hours and work on posts, videos and topics for blogging. I ended up a teary mess because I had no clue what to share! I have many interests and tons of knowledge however, it was hard for me to get it out of my brain and into social media.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Looking back, I know why. I hadn\'t defined my niche. I was trying to market to anyone and everyone who would come across my social media accounts. When I finally realized I had to niche it down, things began to come together and content creation became a breeze!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>First things first. Who is your target audience? (Please don\'t say ANYONE who loves ____! This will only have you pulling out you hair and leave you frustrated and stuck in moving forward in building your brand.) What are their struggles? What solutions can you provide for them? What value can you offer them?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next, once you know who you are marketing to, content is easy. Like, too easy, in my opinion. Let\'s use the example of health and wellness. My niche is women, 30+, who want to feel amazing in their skin, rock their self confidence, attain optimal and vibrant health and create a life that allows them more time with their families. So every time I create a piece of content, I am thinking about these women and how I can help them.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Where do I find content? I keep my eyes open to topics that would be of interest to my niche. Seriously, health and wellness is a billion dollar industry and pretty much every where I go, there\'s information out there. When I\'m at the grocery store, checking out, I see&nbsp;magazine titles. When I\'m on Facebook, I see people posting about their issues. And one of my favorite places is the internet. I will google a few key words and boom! INSTANT IDEAS and CONTENT!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Content creation isn\'t rocket science. It\'s being aware of the trends. It\'s knowing your audience. It\'s adding value with help, support and ideas. Remember, not everyone is in your niche. Not everyone is interested in what you have to offer. And that is 100% ok! Don\'t worry about them. Instead, start calling out your tribe and creating raving fans of your content,,then the sky\'s the limit on the impact you will make!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Receive my free gift - 8 Must Knows for Personal Branding&nbsp;<a href=\"http://bit.ly/7secretssocialmediamakeover\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">HERE</a>!</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Struggling to determine your personal brand? I know the feeling! After almost 2 years of studying and building my own brand, I offer one on one coaching. See if we\'re a good fit by filling out this&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/H8MK97J\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>form</strong></a><a><strong>&nbsp;</strong></a>and I\'ll be in touch with you soon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Content Creation Made Simple', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'personal-branding-on-line-business-network-marketing-personal-branding-on-line-business-content-creation-made-simple', '', '', '2019-02-18 17:19:16', '2019-02-18 17:19:16', '', 0, 'http://handspeak.web-art.net/?p=411', 0, 'post', '', 0),
